snippet.textDisplay:
This is incredibly weak stuff. The headline has the word “testing” in it, but I cannot find any material in the video that merits this categorization. You stick the buds in your ears for a few seconds to confirm they work - great. Have you actually used any of the buds for any length of time to appraise battery life, connectivity, sound quality etc? Do the microphones work? How do they compare in cost? Do any of the AirPods Pro knockoffs have noise cancelling? To me, the utter lack of TESTING puts this video in the close vicinity of clickbait.


But hey — since I’m new here, perhaps I mistook you for a bone fide tech reviewer when in fact all you do is remove shrink wrap from boxes. My apologies if that is the case.
